column4: Top Tesla shareholder says Musk 'doesn't need to be CEO': Barron's
column5: Tesla Inc's largest shareholder expressed its support for Chief Executive Officer Elon Musk  but acknowledged that it was open to a different role for the electric carmaker's founder and CEO  Barron's reported on Tuesday.

column4: Tesla blames misprinted label for China customs hiccup
column5: BENGALURU/SHANGHAI Tesla Inc said on Tuesday that China's customs authorities have accepted the electric carmaker's plan to resolve problems with the clearance of its Model 3 sedans that centered around misprinting of labels.

column4: China suspends customs clearance for Tesla Model 3 imports - Caixin
column5: BEIJING/SHANGHAI  March 5 China's customs authority has suspended customs clearance procedures for Model 3 cars built by Tesla Inc  the financial publication Caixin reported on Tuesday.
